# Product purpose

Full brief: `docs/PRODUCT.md`. Short rules for every change:

## What this is

WhatsApp replacement drive board for ~500–600 drivers. Anyone posts free-text routes (e.g. `Monticello → Brooklyn`); others apply; poster accepts one; passenger phone unlocks only then. Complete → cost + 10% balance to poster (pay outside app); Sunday lock if unsettled. One shared board.

## Non-negotiables

1. **Extremely simple** UI/flows — WhatsApp mental model
2. **Bad-service friendly** — cache board, queue writes, retries, clear offline/pending/synced; Catskills cell is normal
3. **Privacy** — route (+ tags) on board; phone/address only after accept
4. **No in-app payments** — settlement mark only; money moves via Zelle/Venmo/cash

## Drive posts

- Route text required; passenger phone required (hidden until accept); address optional
- Tags: **one-way | round-trip** and **waiting included | waiting not included** (visible on board)
- Not map/GPS posting

## Flow facts

- Apply includes applicant exact location (prefer cached last-known GPS)
- Accept auto-rejects others; unassign allowed; re-assign needs applicant re-confirm
- Complete: cost required; explanation / mileage / waiting free text
- Completed jobs public; posters may hide their posted trips

## Don’t

- Don’t build Uber-style live tracking / map-first routing for v1
- Don’t require good Wi‑Fi then “add offline later” — offline is part of done
- Don’t invent separate roles or multi-group boards for v1
